		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Upscaling the 256x240 pixel texture of the emulated display to 1280x1050* is just drawing one huge quad to the screen. I don't know of any emus that implement NTSC or Scale2x filtering as a pixel shader, or if it's even possible on an Intel GMA.
<br />
<br />
<br />* Yes, 1280. That amount of pillarboxing preserves the 8:7 PAR.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
